headline: Airspace closure halts many Middle East flights after attacks
summary: Airlines canceled 868 flights into Middle East countries on Saturday, according to aviation data firm Cirium.

headline: Why Delta (DAL) Shares Are Getting Obliterated Today
summary: Shares of global airline Delta Air Lines (NYSE:DAL) fell 6.4% in the afternoon session after a surge in crude oil prices sparked concerns about rising jet fuel costs, which could cut into the airline's profits.
